The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Nov. 24: SAIL has proposed to trim its board size by almost a fourth to speed up its decision-making process, official sources said. The plan is to bring down the size of the board between 16 and 18 from the present 24, an official in the steel ministry has said. SAIL has also proposed to change the designation of the companys top executive to chairman and CEO.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 24: Luxury and high-end sedans will be easier to import with the government doing away with safety and emission certificates from the country of origin, but the vehicles must comply with European standards.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 24: Shareholders of the UK-based SAP consultancy Axon have accepted the 441-million ($810.8 million) bid by HCL Technologies, setting the stage for one of the biggest overseas acquisitions by an Indian company.                            
	 Johannesburg, Nov. 24: A Liberian panel has ruled that Delta Mining Consolidated Ltd and Tata Steel may join a re-bidding process for the $1.6-billion Western Cluster iron ore project.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 24: Emami is planning to set up a manufacturing facility in Africa, expected to take off by 2010, as it looks to strengthen its hold in the continent.                                                                                                                         
